  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "Hi all, currently our Database API exposes methods for getting/putting block operations indexed by their room such as:\r\n\r\n```go\r\nVoluntaryExit(ctx context.Context, exitRoot [32]byte) (*ethpb.VoluntaryExit, error)\r\nSaveVoluntaryExit(ctx context.Context, exit *ethpb.VoluntaryExit) error\r\nHasVoluntaryExit(ctx context.Context, exitRoot [32]byte) bool\r\nDeleteVoluntaryExit(ctx context.Context, exitRoot [32]byte) error\r\n```\r\nHowever, this isn't much use, as it makes more sense to have validator index as the key, which opens up a lot more use cases. For example, when archiving information from the state, being able to retrieve the operations that occurred by index is a lot more useful than the roots.\r\n\r\nA PR would modify `VoluntaryExit`, `ProposerSlashing`, `AttesterSlashing`, to utilize validator index as the key in the DB methods.",
